vary on other inputs.
    An annotated corpus comprising some of the various NL input types such as those I discussed in the introduction would go a long way towards giving us a basis against which we could evaluate the generality of our theories.
  
  
    David Carter, Phil Cohen, Nick Haddock, Jerry Hobbs, Aravind Joshi, Don Knuth, Candy Sidner, Phil Stenton, Bonnie Webber, and Steve Whittaker have provided valuable insights toward this endeavor and critical comments on a multiplicity of earlier versions of this paper.
    Steve Whittaker advised me on the statistical analyses.
    I would like to thank Jerry Hobbs for encouraging me to do this in the first place.
  
  
